	<tr id="M12080"><td colspan=1>
		<a name="M12080"></a>
	
		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 width="100%">
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="subjectbar" align=left style="padding:0px;padding-left: 10px;padding-right: 10px;">
		
		&nbsp;</td>
		
	
	<td bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	<td class="subjectbar" height="20" style="font-size: 8pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
		Re: Class Issues List - Update

	</td>
	
		<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">












		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 id="io_bwarriorbalancem12080_table" 
		
			onClick="setId('12080');showLiMenu(this,'io_bwarriorbalancem12080','right',false);" 
			onDblClick="setId('12080');showLiMenu(this,'io_bwarriorbalancem12080','right',false);" 
			
		>
		<tr class=clickable>
			
				<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar_text style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				
			<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='Options' title='Options' width=11 height=28></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		</table>
		
		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=25399'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<img src='/i/rank_icons/admin.gif' border=0 alt=''> <span style='color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; '>Kytherea</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Community Relations Manager<br>
			
				Posts: 7934<br>
				
				Registered: 04-14-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=25399'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=12080#M12080">23</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 4338 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV>1. Taunt:<STRONG>&nbsp;<FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be&nbsp;considered as part of the class re-envisioning</FONT><BR><BR></STRONG>A. Success Rate, particularly against even con mobs and higher is abysmal <FONT color=#0066ff></FONT>B. Taunt Greying out on Out of Range: This has been said to have been something which was supposed to be being fixed, when is this going to happen?<BR><BR>2. Endurance Regen: We need endurance regen from Spells and/or items. Modrods should provide an endurance benefit equal to the mana benefit. Also, change + Endurance only augments to +Endurance regen. Particularly crucial in this is post-resurrection/looting endurance regen.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be&nbsp;considered as part of the class re-envisioning</FONT><BR><BR></STRONG>3. Re-Evaluate warrior disciplines. (currently being evaluated) -- Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning<STRONG> <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be&nbsp;considered as part of the class re-envisioning</FONT><BR></STRONG>There's a few issues: <BR><BR>A. Endurance costs on all of the new discs is WAY too high <STRONG><FONT face=Verdana color=#66cc00 size=2>(Part of the proposed first pass with class re-envisioning posted on EQLive on 3/14/2005)</FONT><BR><BR></STRONG>B. Aura of Runes negates the use of inherent proc right clicks. Please consider "suspending" them rather than dispelling them completely. Furthermore, the rate of fire is too low for it to be worth the endurance spent. Also, please unlink from healing will. being penalized in downtime for invoking something which allows you to survive a fight shouldn't happen.<BR><BR>C. The level 70 discipline needs to be effective against even con and higher mobs. If it's not reasonable to make level 70+ mobs stunnable (and it's probably not reasonable), then change the effect to a dramatic defensive based damage shield (DD) effect, or a "defensive" hate inducing proc, or something along those lines. As it currently stands, there's not a whole lot of use for the discipline which SHOULD be our best. If, as part of the "re-envisioning", stuns work on targets even level or higher, then it needs to fire a LOT more often than it does in order to be useful.<BR><BR>D. Savage onslaught needs a longer timer or shorter refresh and a MUCH lower endurance upkeep.<BR><BR>Update: Please let us know if the "Cleave" effect is working with Savage Onslaught.<BR><BR>4. Warriors need to be distinguished in durability in single group content from knights (and by extension, other classes). Currently, with content being continually tuned downwards, there's nothing which distinguishes warriors from Knights except a lack of ancillary skills. This is particularly true in "non-standard" group configurations (with druids/shamans as primary healers), where knight self-buffs/spells give a tremendous advantage *even in tankability*. Being disadvantaged in durability is unacceptable to warriors who dont' have the luxury of ancillary skills to fall back upon.<STRONG> <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)<!-- / message --><!-- sig --></FONT><BR><BR></STRONG>5. Shields: Please give warriors a reasont o use a shield. Either in "one handed" non dual wielding weapons, or a modifier to one handed weapon damage when a shield is equipped, warriors don't like having a 5% "mitigation' advantage while giving up a 5% avoidance advantage to classes who can contribute in their own survivability, simply because only one class is rendered impotent while using a shield, and the other two aren't.<STRONG> <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT><BR><BR></STRONG>6. Availability of weapons upgrades across the board: Non-raiding warriors are really suffering from a lack of viable upgrades that aren't inferior to 6 expansion old weapons with a recommended level 16 levels below the current "weapon of choice". There really needs to be some movement in weaponry. <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>(currently being evaluated)</STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>7. Mob Summonning Issues: Please make it so that mobs summon rather than in the exact center of their hitbox, in front of them. Being summonned "out of melee range" and turning the mobs all over the place is incredibly frustrating, or better yet make mobs who have been attempted to have been taunted in the last 10 seconds stop summonning. The concept that we're standing in the face of a mob attacking and taunting should be clear indication that we're not trying "to evade" the mobs.<STRONG> <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>8. Downward Scaling Tool:&nbsp; There is a point in EQ where because of the nature of certain spells (Stuns, Tap AA's), warriors take a back seat to Knights of their level at taking melee damage.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In order to remain competitive, warriors need a low end, downward scaling tool which relives this.&nbsp;&nbsp; All of warriors' current tools become more effective the harder the content, but we lack a tool which has strength in weaker content.&nbsp;<STRONG> <FONT color=#3333ff>(new)</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>9.&nbsp; Warriors have been historically an "anti-magic" class, we would like some more innate magical defenses than simply a few points of MR. At higher levels, this is not a meaningful addition. Things we would like to see are things like innate spellshield of 10% at level 70, innate dispel resistance, and other such anti-magic resistances.<STRONG> <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>10. Augments: The addition of vendor based DoN proc augments was great, but there's still a lack of dropped augments, or upgraded effect augments from dropped mobs. This was supposed to have been added in DoN, but none have been found yet. We'd like to see a greater range of dropped hate generating augments.<STRONG>&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></STRONG></DIV></DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Kytherea ~~wielding a giant hammer & a hairless War Hamster~~<br><br>"I'm late, I'm late...."
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
